name: Caroline Johnson
text:
One of the nicest little dog parks I've been to.
Two separate areas, well-maintained and clean (let's try to keep it that way!), benches, water, bags, a couple of little obstacles, landscaping, and good fencing.
Bigger than it looks at first and usually not busy.

name: Lisa King
text: Got bit by someones dog that wasnt on a leash... But overall my dogs love this park...

name: Jamie Peters (ultimatespideylover3)
text: Great place for dogs to roam free!

name: John Senn
text:
Ok. Nice park, but... It's not getting maintained as well as it could be.  Signage is  fading, fence is broken, had to ask the city to please cut the grass (they did as promised), now needs weed eating.

There's only shade on the large dog side.  Need some sail covers for sharing.  It's nice, but with some oversight it could be so much better.

name: Robert Wenner
text: The best place ever.I have a large dog that is a house dog, when he's out he's on a leash or chain this place gives him a hour everyday to run . only thing could make it better if there was a spot where if there were two big dogs they could both go into. now we have to wait til it's empty. But its nice picnic area in the shade or sun benches, water, bags are supplied. Just nice, clean, and close.

name: Lisa Ki
text: Nice fenced activities area.... Places to sit while your dog gets a run... Enjoyable

name: Cyco Pain
text: Not a bad little place for the pups to play.

name: Victory Martinez
text:
Extremely beautiful place.
Safely an alot of green grass

name: Chris Tina Miller
text: Love the agility equipment but needs some upkeep.

name: Scott Killingsworth
text: All the benches are destroyed and rotting, it's mostly just dirt now

name: Crissa Matthew
text: I didn't even know this was a dig park.

name: Mennessia Murphy
text: Needs some minor repairs n more shade.
